                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>4</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="483289" author="paf0186" created="Fri, 9 Jan 2026 20:46:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is likely an excellent candidate for an LLM agent to do - well defined task, structured output, no parallelism, etc.&#160; (I don&apos;t have time, but noting it.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="483288" author="adilger" created="Fri, 9 Jan 2026 20:43:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=simmonsja&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;simmonsja&quot;&gt;simmonsja&lt;/a&gt;, could you please provide some guidance/template here on what needs to be done to add stats exports via Netlink for &lt;tt&gt;jobstats&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;brw_stats&lt;/tt&gt;, and other Lustre parameters/statistics.  Is there a wiki page or other documentation, or some example code on how to access the stats from an application via Netlink?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I found patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/34256&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/34256&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11850&quot; title=&quot;Relocating /proc/fs/lustre/ost to /sys/kernel/debug/lustre/ost prevents non-root access&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11850&quot;&gt;LU-11850&lt;/a&gt; obd: use netlink to get lustre stats&quot;), which may be useful as a starting point.  It appears to me from reading this patch that only stats which are exported via debugfs are accessible via Netlink (i.e. only stats registered via &lt;tt&gt;ldebugfs_stats_alloc()&lt;/tt&gt; are accessible)?  Is there a mechanism to access other parameters (e.g. in sysfs) via Netlink as well, or will everything need to be reworked to hook into &lt;tt&gt;lstats_list&lt;/tt&gt; in order to be accessible via Netlink?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Are the stats registered through &lt;tt&gt;ldebugfs_stats_alloc()&lt;/tt&gt; accessible as structured YAML objects, or is it a plain-text dump of the stats as they would appear in debugfs?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
